# Git Branch Workflow

NEVER push directly to `main`. Always:

1. Create a descriptive feature branch: `git checkout -b <branch-name>`
2. Commit changes to that branch
3. Push the branch: `git push origin <branch-name>`
4. Let the user merge via PR on GitHub

This applies to ALL changes — even small fixes — so every change is reviewable and revertable before it hits main.
